### RFID Manager — manual API smoke test
### Open this file with the "REST Client" VS Code extension (humao.rest-client)
### and click "Send Request" above each block. Run the server first
### (see .vscode/tasks.json: "Server: dev", or F5 > "Server: Debug (tsx)"),
### then seed it once with `npm run prisma:seed` inside server/.
###
### Auth is two steps (see README.md's "Full stack" section): sign in to get
### a session token, then mint a short-lived JWT from that session — the JWT
### is what every other request below authenticates with.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api

### Health check (no auth)
GET http://localhost:4000/health

### Sign in as the seeded company admin — captures the session token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme-logistics.example",
  "password": "ChangeMe123!"
}

### Mint a JWT from that session — this is the token every request below uses
# @name jwt
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/token
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### Who am I
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### Dashboard stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### List cards
GET {{baseUrl}}/cards?pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### Register a new card
# @name registerCard
POST {{baseUrl}}/cards
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "uid": "04AABBCCEE",
  "cardType": "NTAG213",
  "label": "REST Client test card"
}

### Block the card just created
POST {{baseUrl}}/cards/{{registerCard.response.body.id}}/block
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### List notifications (the block above should have generated one)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### List card holders
GET {{baseUrl}}/holders
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### List encoders
GET {{baseUrl}}/encoders
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### Audit log
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs?pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt.response.body.token}}

### Active sessions for the current user — this one uses the *session*
### token directly (list-sessions/revoke-session/sign-out/change-password/
### update-user are better-auth's own endpoints and don't accept the JWT)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/list-sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### --- Super admin flow ---

# @name superLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@rfidmanager.local",
  "password": "ChangeMe123!"
}

# @name superJwt
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/token
Authorization: Bearer {{superLogin.response.body.token}}

### List every company (super admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/companies
Authorization: Bearer {{superJwt.response.body.token}}
